reviewText:
An awful sequel to one of the best MMOs I've ever played. This game brings shame to the original Ragnar√∂k, which gave many of us MMORPGers our very first taste of what it is to play a MMORPG. Comparisons aside, Ragnarok Online 2 is still a very bad game.

When the game was released in 2013, I've played a few hours and thought that the game itself was kinda generic and a bland MMO but I wanted to give RO2 the benefit of the doubt and I kept playing for something like three months or so (I've probably had around 300 hours of gameplay outside Steam).

As soon as I found that this game was in Steam, I felt like I should came here and make a short review of what RO2 includes. Let's resume it in a few words:

- A horrible pay2win system and a ridiculous amount of grinding to earn enough money to catch up with those who can buy from the cash shop;

- Generic anime graphics;

- A lot of bugs that are never or take a hell of a long amount of time to get fixed;

- Unbalanced classes and a repetitive combat system;

- Generic Quests. A lot of them. Bring X, Kill X monsters, etc.


Just stay away from it. This game is a failure and doesn't worth your time.

RPGs aren't hard;
they need care and attention.
This game has neither

